        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Digital Breast Tomosynthesis: Update on Technology, Evidence, and                    Clinical Practice" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Yiming  Gao" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Linda  Moy" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Samantha                            L.  Heller" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Digital breast tomosynthesis has improved the sensitivity and specificity of mammography, yielding a sustainable increase in detection of invasive cancer without increased detection of in situ cancers." /><meta name="Description" content="Digital breast tomosynthesis has improved the sensitivity and specificity of mammography, yielding a sustainable increase in detection of invasive cancer without increased detection of in situ cancers." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="Digital breast tomosynthesis (DBT) has been widely adopted in breast imaging in both screening and diagnostic settings. The benefits of DBT are well established. Compared with two-dimensional digit..." /><meta name="Description" content="Digital breast tomosynthesis (DBT) has been widely adopted in breast imaging in both screening and diagnostic settings. The benefits of DBT are well established. Compared with two-dimensional digit..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content=" Radiological Society of North America " /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2021-02-05" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="200101" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.2021200101" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="url" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2021200101" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.2021200101" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta name="d